# Cursor Rule: Collision & Session Awareness

Before editing any file in this repo, Cursor agents must check for active write leases.

## Pre-write gate

Run before writing to any file:
```
python scripts/file_collision_gate.py check --paths <target-file> --agent cursor
```

If the result is `"status": "blocked"`, **do not write**. Surface the conflict list to the user and stop.

## Session awareness

To see all active sessions (terminals, agents, worktrees) at once:
```
python scripts/session_status.py
```

To see all currently lease-blocked paths:
```
python scripts/file_collision_gate.py list-blocked
```

To cross-check in-progress beads against active leases:
```
python scripts/bead_collision_gate.py status
```

## Rules

- Never write to a file another session has an active write or exclusive lease on.
- If `file_collision_gate.py` is unavailable (import error, missing deps), fail open and warn the user.
- Do not acquire a lease on behalf of the user — leases are acquired by autonomous harness scripts only.
- If two Cursor windows are open on this repo, one should be on a dedicated worktree branch.
